.SH NAME
cert-stealchain - Retrieve and save the full certificate chain from a TLS host


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcert stealchain 
\[la]host:port\[ra] [more ...] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Connect to one or more TLS endpoints and write the presented
certificate chain to a local PEM file named \&.pem.

.PP
Use --sni-name to override the SNI name used for the TLS handshake. Root CAs
are taken from --ca if provided, otherwise from the system pool.


